CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 3, 1961, pg. 16 reads: "Talented - Elsie Garner, one of two Negroes in a junior class of 87 [?] at St. Paul Cathedral High School, was awarded a certificate of scholarship and elected to the Student Council, to the Historiana Society, and to the Pen and Scroll Society for achieving a minimum of 75 inches of print in school newspaper. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Elsie Garner wearing dark floral jumper and light colored blouse, seated on arm of upholstered chair in front of light colored background
